# Gotya Text Anonymizer

Gotya Text Anonymizer is a Python package that helps you to anonymize text by detecting and redacting personally identifiable information (PII) such as names, addresses, phone numbers, credit card numbers, email addresses, and more.

## Installation

To install the Gotya Text Anonymizer package, run the following command:

```bash
pip install gotya-text-anonymizer
```


## Usage

Here's an example of how to use the Gotya Text Anonymizer package:

```python
from gotya_text_anonymizer.anonymizer import main

text = """My name is gotya tech and I live in Berlin, credit card 1234567890123456, 
Phone Number: +441234567890, Address: 123 Main St, Anytown, UK, 
Email: johndoe@example.com, PIN: 8888, CVV: 123"""
threshold = 0.3

redacted_text = main(text, threshold)
print(redacted_text)


This will print the redacted text with PII replaced by tags. You can customize the threshold value to control the confidence level of the detected entities.

```


